NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_oam_config_msg

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This procedure will configure OAM loopback and linktrace messages on MEPs.The MEPs that will be used to configure OAM messages on will can be determined in two ways

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_oam_config_msg

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

See description of -handle parameter for more details.

Valid options are:

create

create messages

modify

not supported

reset

disables all messages and all TLVs.

DEFAULT

 None

-port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Parameter -port_handle specifies the port on which to configure OAM messages. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN.The messages will be configured on the MEPs from port -port_handle.

DEFAULT

 None

-count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Determines the number of messages to configure.Dependencies: -mep_id must not exist or -mep_id_incr_mode is not 'list'

DEFAULT

1

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Parameter handle can be a bridge handle returned by ::::emulation_oam_config_topology or a port handle returned by ::::connect. This parameter can be used when mode is 'reset'. If this parameter is a port handle, all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Points from all the bridges on this port will be disabled. If this parameter is a bridge handle all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Pointson this bridge will be disabled. If this parameter is not used on -mode 'reset', Maintenace Points will be filtered the same way as for -mode 'create' and the messages and TLVs on the filtered MPs will be disabled.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is used to select the MEPs to configure message on when -mep_id parameter is not specified.To configure messages on MEPs independent of their mac address identifier see the description for -mac_local_list parameter.If this parameter is not specified messages will be configured on MEPs independent of their mac_local address.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local_incr_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -mep_id is not specified.

Valid options are:

none

(DEFAULT) mac_local value will not be modified (all messages will be configured on the MEPs having the same mac address)

increment

increment mac_local address MEP identifier a number of times equal to -count,

decrement

decrement mac_local address MEP identifier a number of times

list

Use the values specified with -mac_local_list as MEP identifiers.

random

Generate a random mac_local address MEP identifier for every message.

DEFAULT

none

-mac_local_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -mep_id is not specified.Dependencies: -mac_local_incr_mode list.This parameter must either be a list of MAC addresses or the keyword "all". When the keyword "all" is used -mac_local will not be used as identified for MEPs.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local_repeat

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -mep_id is not specified.Dependencies: -mac_local_incr_mode increment | decrement.The number of times to use the mac_local address MEP identifier before incrementing or decrementing

DEFAULT

1

-mac_local_step

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -mep_id is not specified.Dependencies: -mac_local_incr_mode increment | decrement.The step to increment | decrement mac_local address MEP identifier.

DEFAULT

00:00:00:00:00:01

-mac_remote

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter configures the destination of the OAM messages. To send to all destinations see the description for -mac_remote_list parameter.If this parameter is not specified, messages will be sent to all destinations.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_remote_incr_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Not defined

Valid options are:

none

(DEFAULT) mac_remote value will not be modified (all messages will be configured with -mac_remote destination address)

increment

increment mac_remote address a number of times equal to -count.

decrement

decrement mac_remote address

list

Use the values specified with -mac_remote_list as OAM message destinations.

random

Generate a random mac_local address OAM message destination for every message.

DEFAULT

none

-mac_remote_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Dependencies: -mac_remote_incr_mode list.This parameter must either be a list of MAC addresses or the keyword "all". When the keyword "all" is used -mac_remote will not be used as OAM Message destination address and the message will be sent to all destinations.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_remote_repeat

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Dependencies: -mac_remote_incr_mode increment | decrement.The number of times to use the mac_remote OAM message destination address before incrementing or decrementing

DEFAULT

1

-mac_remote_step

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Dependencies: -mac_remote_incr_mode increment | decrement.The step to increment | decrement mac_remote OAM message destination address.

DEFAULT

00:00:00:00:00:01

-msg_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the timeout duration before messages are deemed lost (in milliseconds).The timeout will be rounded to the closest equivalent measured in seconds. This value should be less than -renew_period. If a greater value than -renew_period is configured it will be forced to be equal to -renew_period.

DEFAULT

5000

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

loopback - (DEFAULT) configure loopback messageslinktrace - configure linktrace messagestest - not supported

DEFAULT

loopback

-oam_standard

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -mep_id is not specified. Filter MEPs that will be used to configure OAM messages on by their oam standard.

Valid options are:

1ag

(DEFAULT) IEEE standard

itut_y1731

ITU-T standard

DEFAULT

ieee_802.1ag

-renew_test_msgs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Flag to indicate that messages should be sent periodically.

DEFAULT

 None

-renew_period

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the timeout duration before resending messages (in milliseconds). The value will be rounded to the closest equivalent measured in seconds. This value should be greater than -msg_timeout. If a smaller value than -msg_timeout is configured, the value of -msg_timeout will be forced to be equal to -renew_timer.

DEFAULT

90000

-handle_granularity

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Defines how message handles will be returned. Message handles can be used with ::::emulation_oam_config_msg to retrieve per session message statistics for a specific message or a group of messages.One MEP can be configured with a maximum of two messages: one linktrace and one loopback. Notes: A message can be refered by only one message handle no matter what the type of the message handle is (per_message or per_group). If seperate calls to emulation_oam_config_msg procedure configure messages on MEPs that already have those messages configured, the last call will overwrite the former message handle with the new message handle and print a warning informing the user about this.

Valid options are:

per_message

one handle for each message created. The number of message

x

one handle for each message created. The number of message

per_group

one handle for all the messages created withing the current procedure call. Based

DEFAULT

per_group

-mep_id

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

When this parameter is used, MEPs that will be used to configure OAM Messages on will be filtered based on -port_handle, -bridge_id and -mep_id. To configure OAM messages independant of the Mep ID see description for mep_id_list parameter.

DEFAULT

 None

DEFAULT

none

DEFAULT

count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Determines the number of messages to configure.Dependencies: -mep_id must not exist or -mep_id_incr_mode is not 'list'

DEFAULT

1

handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Parameter handle can be a bridge handle returned by ::::emulation_oam_config_topology or a port handle returned by ::::connect. This parameter can be used when mode is 'reset'. If this parameter is a port handle, all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Points from all the bridges on this port will be disabled. If this parameter is a bridge handle all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Pointson this bridge will be disabled. If this parameter is not used on -mode 'reset', Maintenace Points will be filtered the same way as for -mode 'create' and the messages and TLVs on the filtered MPs will be disabled.

DEFAULT

 None

handle_granularity

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Defines how message handles will be returned. Message handles can be used with ::::emulation_oam_config_msg to retrieve per session message statistics for a specific message or a group of messages.One MEP can be configured with a maximum of two messages: one linktrace and one loopback. Notes: A message can be refered by only one message handle no matter what the type of the message handle is (per_message or per_group). If seperate calls to emulation_oam_config_msg procedure configure messages on MEPs that already have those messages configured, the last call will overwrite the former message handle with the new message handle and print a warning informing the user about this.

Valid options are:

per_message

one handle for each message created. The number of message

x

one handle for each message created. The number of message

per_group

one handle for all the messages created withing the current procedure call. Based

DEFAULT

per_group

Supported platforms Details

DESCRIPTION

Determines the number of messages to configure.Dependencies: -mep_id must not exist or -mep_id_incr_mode is not 'list'

handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Parameter handle can be a bridge handle returned by ::::emulation_oam_config_topology or a port handle returned by ::::connect. This parameter can be used when mode is 'reset'. If this parameter is a port handle, all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Points from all the bridges on this port will be disabled. If this parameter is a bridge handle all messages and all TLVs from all the Maintenance Pointson this bridge will be disabled. If this parameter is not used on -mode 'reset', Maintenace Points will be filtered the same way as for -mode 'create' and the messages and TLVs on the filtered MPs will be disabled.

 None

handle_granularity

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Defines how message handles will be returned. Message handles can be used with ::::emulation_oam_config_msg to retrieve per session message statistics for a specific message or a group of messages.One MEP can be configured with a maximum of two messages: one linktrace and one loopback. Notes: A message can be refered by only one message handle no matter what the type of the message handle is (per_message or per_group). If seperate calls to emulation_oam_config_msg procedure configure messages on MEPs that already have those messages configured, the last call will overwrite the former message handle with the new message handle and print a warning informing the user about this.

Valid options are:

per_message

one handle for each message created. The number of message

x

one handle for each message created. The number of message

per_group

one handle for all the messages created withing the current procedure call. Based

DEFAULT

per_group

NOTES

IxNetwork

1. If all filter parameter are specified as lists, parameter -count will be ignored and the number of messages to be configured will be set by the length of the shortest list parameter. If all filter parameters are configured as 'all', the count parameter will be forced to value 1.

IxNetwork

2. If a filter parameter is not specified at all it will behave as an 'include all' filter.
